# Python Pipeline
## Customer Churn Intelligence Platform

This folder contains the complete **end-to-end Python analytics pipeline** — from synthetic data generation through EDA, feature engineering, ML modelling, SHAP explainability, and production scoring.

---

## Pipeline Scripts

| Script | Purpose | Run Order |
|--------|---------|-----------|
| `01_data_generation.py` | Generates 10,000-customer synthetic dataset with embedded causal churn model | 1st |
| `02_eda_analysis.py` | Full exploratory data analysis — distributions, cohort heatmap, correlation matrix | 2nd |
| `03_feature_engineering.py` | Builds 47 ML-ready features from raw signals | 3rd |
| `04_churn_model.py` | Trains and evaluates 4 ML algorithms, selects best model | 4th |
| `05_model_explainability.py` | SHAP global + local explanations, feature importance charts | 5th |
| `06_scoring_pipeline.py` | Production scoring — outputs churn_scores.csv with risk tiers and actions | 6th |
| `churn_analysis_full.py` | **Single-file version** — all 6 steps in one script (for Kaggle / demo use) | Any |

---

## Quick Start

```bash
# 1. Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/Rabbani-bot/churn-intelligence.git
cd churn-intelligence

# 2. Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate        # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

# 3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 4. Run the full pipeline (single command)
python python/churn_analysis_full.py

# All figures → reports/figures/
# Scoring output → data/processed/churn_scores.csv
```

