## Model Architecture

```
Raw Data (10,000 customers × 24 features)
    │
    ▼
Feature Engineering (47 features)
    ├── Engagement signals    (login freq, adoption rate, session depth)
    ├── Commercial signals    (MRR, contract type, payment delays)
    ├── Support signals       (ticket volume, resolution time, CSAT)
    ├── Sentiment signals     (NPS score, CSM coverage)
    └── Derived risk scores   (composite risk, flag counts)
    │
    ▼
SMOTE (class balancing — training set only)
    │
    ▼
Model Benchmarking
    ├── Logistic Regression   AUC-ROC: 0.847
    ├── Random Forest         AUC-ROC: 0.891
    ├── Gradient Boosting     AUC-ROC: 0.908
    └── XGBoost ★ (selected)  AUC-ROC: 0.923
    │
    ▼
SHAP Explainability
    ├── Global feature importance (all customers)
    └── Individual waterfall plots (per customer)
    │
    ▼
Scoring Output (churn_scores.csv)
    ├── churn_probability     (0.0 – 1.0)
    ├── risk_tier             (Critical / High / Medium / Low)
    ├── revenue_at_risk       (MRR × churn_probability)
    └── recommended_action    (intervention type)
```

