## Random Seeds & Reproducibility

All experiments use `RANDOM_STATE = 42`. Every run produces identical results on identical library versions.

```python
RANDOM_STATE = 42
np.random.seed(RANDOM_STATE)
# SMOTE, train_test_split, XGBoost all use RANDOM_STATE
```

